'''Hugh C. Graham, Jr''' is an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]]. He competed as a singles skater and as a pair skater with his sister, [[Margaret Anne Graham]]. After his competitive career ended, he spent several years as the President of the [[United States Figure Skating Association]] (1986-89).<ref name="pres1">(9 January 2004). [http://www.usfsa.org/Story.asp?id=20866 Six Individuals Inducted Into U.S. Hall of Fame], ''[[U.S. Figure Skating]]'' website, Retrieved December 21, 2010</ref>
He was inducted into the [[United States Figure Skating Hall of Fame]] in 2004.<ref name="pres1"/>
